I want to make minecraft animations, using Blender, but I am not so sure as to how to change my skin.

But I know that the skin will not turn out well if I use that format.
So...could someone help me out?
I'll send you two pictures!

1st picture: When I put the normal skin in Blender
2nd picture: My normal minecraft skin

Thank you!

Bye!
Best Regards,

replies.body:
I have no idea about how Blender interprets image files, but from experience I suggest you turn it off and on again ;).
But maybe try saving the skin file in a different format i.e. jpeg or png and then re-upload it using Blender. 

Have you tried setting up a new projects and using a different skin, this way you can abstract the source of the problem. If it won't work with a new project and a different skin then its ever you doing something wrong or the program and not the skin. 

If it work I guess then there is a problem the skin you are using; something conflicting with the skin in the existing project. 

Good Lock with this anyway!!
